LO IMPORTANT ÉS CREAR UN DESIGN SYSTEM

Refactor ProjectCard component (project-card.ts and project-card.html) to remove DaisyUI styling and prepare it for a custom Tailwind design system.

Requirements:

1. Remove ALL DaisyUI classes (bg-base-*, card, btn, dropdown, etc.)
2. Replace them with Tailwind utility classes using a custom theme with these tokens:
   - bg → #0F172A
   - surface → #111827
   - surface2 → #1F2937
   - text → #E2E8F0
   - primary → #14B8A6
   - accent → #60A5FA

3. Do NOT introduce random colors (no purple, no indigo, no default Tailwind colors like blue-500 unless mapped to tokens)

4. Keep the layout and structure the same, but:
   - simplify the HTML
   - improve readability
   - avoid duplicated logic

5. Move any conditional logic or formatting out of the template into the component (TypeScript)

6. Prepare the component for E2E testing:
   - add data-testid attributes to key elements:
     - project-card
     - project-menu
     - project-title

7. Keep Angular control flow syntax (@if, @for)

8. Do NOT add new features, only refactor

Goal:
A clean, maintainable Angular component that uses Tailwind with design tokens instead of DaisyUI, ready for consistent theming and Playwright testing.

